headline: Energy Sector Drags as Oil Prices Weigh on Profits
summary: The energy sector is dragging down the S&P 500’s Q2 earnings, with a projected -24% YoY profit drop due to lower oil prices.

headline: 2 Cash-Heavy Stocks on Our Buy List and 1 We Find Risky
summary: Companies with more cash than debt can be financially resilient, but that doesn’t mean they’re all strong investments. Some lack leverage because they struggle to grow or generate consistent profits, making them unattractive borrowers.
